7 Examining packages
********************

There is an option to make use of the "extraction mode" which serves to
examine binary packages for debugging purposes.  The extraction mode
consists of decompressing a package into a single directory, verifying
its integrity and preserving its properties.

     qi -x mksh-R56c-x86_64+1.tlz

   This action will put the content of "mksh-R56c-x86_64+1.tlz" into a
single directory, which is a private directory for the user who
requested the action, creation mode will be equal to *u=,g=rwx,o=rwx
(0700)*.  The package content will reside on this location, default mask
to deploy the content will be equal to *u=rwx,g=rwx,o=rwx (0000)*.

   The creation of the custom directory is influenced by the value of
the 'TMPDIR' variable.


